education.title: Cornell University
education.subtitle: Computer Science, College of Engineering
workDescription: Cornell Hyperloop project team: I worked on the electrical team in the GUI subteam. We worked on coming up with visualizers to track battery cell data. I worked on cross-disciplinary collaboration, teamwork, and practiced working in an agile development pattern.

Sigma Delta Tau: As the panhellenic representative on executive board for Sigma Delta Tau, I met weekly with representatives from every other sorority on campus to discuss prominent issues in greek life and advocate for the women in my community.

Society of Women Engineers: On the alumni relations committee for SWE at Cornell I was able to help plan networking events and communication streams between students and alumni in the organization to help cultivate a community of empowered female engineers.

Cornell Medium Design Collective: Working with a team of designers to conduct interviews and research for a proposed semesterly project. Our most recent project was a spotify redesign that allowed for easier music sharing and the creation of music auras. Developed UI/UX eye and creativity in design.
Cornell Varsity Sailing Team: Spent time as a student Athlete training and competing for Cornell's Varsity Sailing Team as a crew.

Study Abroad: Spent the semester studying at the University of Edinburgh where I was able to integrate myself into a different community and make connections and relationships with Computer Scientists and other students from across the world.
Women in Computing at Cornell: General Assembly member.
